Let $a, b, c$ be the roots of $x^3 + 2x^2 + 5x + 7 = 0.$ i.e. $a, b, c$ satisfy this equation. We have
\begin{align*}
\frac{1}{a} + \frac{1}{b} + \frac{1}{c} &= \frac{ab+ac+bc}{abc}\\
&= \frac{5}{\text{-}7}\\
&= \boxed{-\frac{5}{7}}.
\end{align*}

